    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This interview was conducted by Albert Ruben on September 4, 2001. In this interview Natalia Schriffin talks about how she helped Alger Hiss transcribe his memoir and later became one of his readers. Schriffin explains that she was recruited by Victor Navasky in the summer of 1985 to help Hiss transcribe his book Recollections of a Life, and after the book was finished began reading to him regularly.  She talks about meeting the other young people who read for Hiss and her impression that he had a genuine interest in young people and their ideas. Much of the interview focuses on her perception of Hiss's personality. She also shares some stories about helping Hiss and his wife Isabel at their home.</field>
